    // Implement custom handle here
  }
}
```

2. Pass an instance of your custom `SelectionControls` subclass to the `TextField` widget's `selectionControls` property:

```dart
TextField(
  decoration: InputDecoration(
    hintText: 'Enter some text',
  ),
  selectionControls: CustomTextSelectionControls(),
);
```

The `CustomTextSelectionControls` subclass overrides the `buildToolbar` and `buildHandle` methods to provide custom implementations of the toolbar and handle. You can use these methods to provide your own widgets for the handle and toolbar.

For example, you can replace the default text selection handle with an icon:

```dart
@override
Widget buildHandle(BuildContext context, TextSelectionHandleType type, double textLineHeight) {
 double handleSize = textLineHeight * 2;
 return Icon(Icons.drag_handle, size: handleSize);
}
```

Or if you prefer to use the default handle and just want to customize its appearance:

```dart
@override
