To create a custom shape that includes both a line and a circle in Flutter, you can use a `CustomPainter` and draw the line and circle using the `Canvas.drawCircle` and `Canvas.drawLine` methods.

Here's an example that draws a line and a circle together:

```dart
class CustomShapePainter extends CustomPainter {
  @override
  void paint(Canvas canvas, Size size) {
    double centerX = size.width / 2;
    double centerY = size.height / 2;
    double radius = 20.0;

    Paint circlePaint = Paint()
      ..color = Colors.blue
      ..style = PaintingStyle.fill;

    Paint linePaint = Paint()
      ..color = Colors.blue
      ..strokeWidth = 4.0;

    // Draw a line from left to right
    canvas.drawLine(Offset(0, centerY), Offset(size.width, centerY), linePaint);

    // Draw a circle at the center of the line
    canvas.drawCircle(Offset(centerX, centerY), radius, circlePaint);
  }

  @override
  bool shouldRepaint(CustomPainter oldDelegate) {
    return false;
  }
}
```

In this example, we're creating a `CustomPainter` subclass called `CustomShapePainter`. The `paint` method is called whenever the shape needs to be drawn. 

We first set the `centerX`, `centerY`, and `radius` values for the circle. We then create `Paint` objects for the circle and line. The `color` property of the circle paint is set to blue, and the `style` property is set to `PaintingStyle.fill`. The line paint's `color` property is also set to blue, and its `strokeWidth` property is set to 4.0.

We then draw a line from the left side of the canvas to the right using `canvas.drawLine`, passing in two `Offset` objects. The first `Offset` object is `Offset(0, centerY)`, which will be the starting point of the line. The `centerY` value is used as the vertical position of the line. The second `Offset` object is `Offset(size.width, centerY)`, which will be the end point of the line. The `size.width` value is used as the horizontal position of the line.

Finally, we draw a circle at the center of the line using `canvas.drawCircle`, passing in an `Offset` object for the center of the circle and the `radius` value. The `circlePaint` object is used to draw the circle.

